wouldn&rsquo;t know Ted you big bollocks.&rdquo;</span>\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&ldquo;What? Have you been reading those Roddy Doyle books again, Dougal?&rdquo;</span>\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&ldquo;I have yeah Ted, you big gobshite.&rdquo;</span>\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&ldquo;Yes, well that&rsquo;s all very well, but you have to remember, they&rsquo;re just stories. Normal people like us don&rsquo;t use that kind of language. Remember, this is the real world.&rdquo;</span>\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Roddy Doyle is a man who&rsquo;s often come under fire in the past for a perception of the &lsquo;real world&rsquo; that, for some, cuts too close to the bone. Indeed, it was on such a basis that he was once told by a film producer that the &lsquo;fuck quotient&rsquo; in one particular novel was far too high for the big screen. </span>\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Last Tuesday, he made an appearance at the Hist. He was presented with the Edmund Burke medal for his contribution to the arts before addressing the crowd.</span>\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">His subject of choice &ndash; for a change &ndash; was the economic climate, but he had rather a different take on the subject than that to which we have become so nauseatingly used. &lsquo;I don&rsquo;t want to say anything profound or deep,&rsquo; he began, &lsquo;But there seems to be a perception that there is nothing in Ireland for you.&rsquo; He condemned the &lsquo;walking picture of hopelessness&rsquo; that he feels the country has become, insisting that great stories are often written in hard times. &lsquo;And at the same time, we have more to offer the world than culture alone.&rsquo;</span>\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> </span>\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_1544\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"300\" caption=\"&lsquo;You have to get to know things in other ways; find the emotions within yourself.&rsquo;\"]<a href=\"http://www.universitytimes.ie/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/BEADLE_RODDYDOYLE_0091.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-1544\" title=\"BEADLE_RODDYDOYLE_0091\" src=\"http://www.universitytimes.ie/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/BEADLE_RODDYDOYLE_0091-300x185.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"185\" /></a>[/caption]\n\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&lsquo;The notion that Ireland has nothing to offer the world anymore is warped,&rsquo; he asserted, &lsquo;Fight it. Fight it by laughing. Sure the country doesn&rsquo;t like you (young people) anyway. You&rsquo;ve no manners, no attention span, no time for anything but facebook, and as for your morals&hellip;!&rsquo;</span>\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Having conveyed his Obama-esque message of hope to the room of eager onlookers, Mr Doyle proceeded to take questions on everything from the origins of his desire to write &ndash; reading &ndash; to the differences between Dublin of yesteryear and Dublin of today &ndash; not much: &lsquo;A joke is still a joke. Grief is still grief. Joy is still joy.&rsquo; &ndash; to the process of turning his works into films. Each answer was considered, yet thoroughly unassuming.</span>\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Interestingly, he dismissed the old mantra that one should only write what one knows, describing it as &lsquo;far too limiting&rsquo;. Applying such a rule to himself, he held, would allow him write about the experiences of a 52 year old, short sighted man and nothing else. Under such a condition, &lsquo;Snapper&rsquo; &ndash; a novel centred on the life of a pregnant girl &ndash; could never have been written because, as he simply put it, &lsquo;I&rsquo;ve never been pregnant&rsquo;. &lsquo;You have to get to know things in other ways; find the emotions within yourself.&rsquo;</span>\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">On that note of poignancy, auditor Huw Duffy called time. The show was over, and the ever amicable Roddy Doyle descended into the rabble for a chat.</span>\n</div>\n</div>", "Imageurl": "1542", "Thumb_nail": "http://universitytimes.ie/wp-content/uploads/2013/utlogo.jpg", "ID": "1541", "Heading": "The Hist welcomes Roddy Doyle"}